{
  "text": "Most bullying occurs at school, rather than on the way to or from school. Assailants and victims are generally in the same grade level, and while minors are supposed to be supervised at school, most episodes of harassment are not known to teachers and the victim usually feels unable to report them to these and their parents. [CITATION_1] reported that the prevalence of bullying in 40 countries with representative national samples was 8.6% to 45.2% in males and 4.8%",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "2175615"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "2175615": {
      "title": "A Cross-National Profile of Bullying and Victimization among Adolescents in 40 Countries",
      "abstract": "Objectives: ::: (1) To compare the prevalence of bullying and victimization among boys and girls and by age in 40 countries. (2) In 6 countries, to compare rates of direct physical, direct verbal, and indirect bullying by gender, age, and country."
    }
  }
